    <h2 class="section-heading reveal">Abstract</h2>

    <div class="prose reveal">
      <!-- TODO: Replace with your actual problem statement paragraph 1 -->
      <p>
         Mobile robots operate in dynamic, uncertain environments where rare failures and near-misses are inevitable. Yet, reconstructing what truly happened remains a fundamental challenge.
      </p>
      <p>
      Existing approaches are limited in three key ways:

(1) Incomplete evidence: External sensors miss internal autonomy states and decisions.
(2) Infeasible always-on recording: Full-resolution logging exceeds onboard compute and storage budgets.
(3) Distorted replay under vibration: Motion-induced artifacts corrupt sensor data, causing replay to diverge from real behavior.

These limitations make failure analysis unreliable and hinder continuous system improvement.
      </p>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>








